1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,901
Rrator: Previously on
"jojo’s bizarre adventure"...

2
00:00:03,237 --> 00:00:05,339
♪♪

3
00:00:07,641 --> 00:00:08,642
( Iggy yelps )

4
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:17,351
( Yells ) Blast it!

5
00:00:17,384 --> 00:00:19,820
oh, no!
The exit’s blocked with ice,

6
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:22,456
and more’s coming this way!

7
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:24,558
Shit!

8
00:00:26,293 --> 00:00:28,428
It’s starting to cover
the whole tunnel.

9
00:00:28,462 --> 00:00:31,231
I gotta find a way out
of this deathtrap!

10
00:00:31,265 --> 00:00:32,399
( Horus squawks )

11
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:34,501
( Iggy groans )

12
00:00:37,437 --> 00:00:39,372
( Gasps ) What?!

13
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:40,474
( Grunts )

14
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:41,475
My paw!

15
00:00:41,508 --> 00:00:43,276
( Pet shop trills )

16
00:00:43,310 --> 00:00:45,546
Iggy: I can’t pry my paw loose!

17
00:00:45,579 --> 00:00:47,748
( Pet shop warbles )

18
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:53,553
( Iggy screams )

19
00:00:55,255 --> 00:00:56,790
( Pet shop warbles )

20
00:01:02,496 --> 00:01:04,498
♪

21
00:01:16,143 --> 00:01:17,811
( Warbles )

22
00:01:18,846 --> 00:01:20,848
♪

23
00:01:22,883 --> 00:01:24,885
( Singing in Japanese )

24
00:01:43,904 --> 00:01:45,906
♪

25
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:49,376
Joseph: Hmm.

26
00:01:49,409 --> 00:01:51,845
all right,
the sun is about to set.

27
00:01:51,879 --> 00:01:53,748
Polnareff: Didn’t "shades"
say three hours?

28
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:56,650
Guess that cocky beggar
had a bit more trouble

29
00:01:56,683 --> 00:01:58,418
finding dio’s mansion
than he thought.

30
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:01,221
Can’t say I was expecting
this to happen, though.

31
00:02:01,255 --> 00:02:03,424
Right, avdol?

32
00:02:03,457 --> 00:02:05,626
Avdol: I have a bad feeling.

33
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:08,729
Maybe it’s better if he doesn’t
find that accursed mansion.

34
00:02:08,762 --> 00:02:09,863
- Joseph: Hmm?
- Jotaro: Hmm?

35
00:02:09,897 --> 00:02:11,465
- Polnareff: Hmm?
- Avdol: You see,

36
00:02:11,498 --> 00:02:13,266
maybe he hasn’t come back,

37
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,136
- because he did find it.
- ( Both grunt )

38
00:02:16,170 --> 00:02:17,705
Polnareff: What are you saying?

39
00:02:17,738 --> 00:02:20,341
Avdol: It didn’t occur to me
until a moment ago,

40
00:02:20,374 --> 00:02:23,177
but a stand user is likely
to be guarding dio’s lair.

41
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:26,246
We may have put that beggar’s
life in grave danger,

42
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,149
if he hasn’t
already been killed.

43
00:02:28,182 --> 00:02:30,718
Polnareff: What?
Are you serious?

44
00:02:30,751 --> 00:02:32,753
♪

45
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:38,859
( Water flowing )

46
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:47,668
( Heavy breathing )

47
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:01,916
Iggy: Son of a--i barely
made it out of there,

48
00:03:01,949 --> 00:03:04,618
and my--my leg is--

49
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:08,221
that ice caught my paw
like a bear trap.

50
00:03:08,255 --> 00:03:10,758
i’d be dead
if I hadn’t gnawed it off.

51
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:13,961
I-I think i’m gonna
hide out here for a while.

52
00:03:13,994 --> 00:03:17,331
If i’m down here long enough,
maybe birdbrain’ll go away.

53
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:19,199
After this is over,

54
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:22,570
the speedwagon foundation
can make me an artificial leg.

55
00:03:22,603 --> 00:03:24,605
But i’m still pissed as hell.

56
00:03:24,638 --> 00:03:25,772
Damn that bird.

57
00:03:25,806 --> 00:03:27,775
you’re not
getting away with this!

58
00:03:27,808 --> 00:03:31,211
I’m gonna make you suffer
for what you did to me.

59
00:03:31,245 --> 00:03:32,246
Just you wait.

60
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:34,848
Wait. That sound.

61
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:37,585
Something out there
dove into the water.

62
00:03:37,618 --> 00:03:39,987
♪

63
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:41,355
No way.

64
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:43,624
narrator:
Birds have the capacity

65
00:03:43,657 --> 00:03:44,925
to dive under water.

66
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:46,860
Like humans and canines,

67
00:03:46,894 --> 00:03:50,531
birds are reliant upon lungs
for respiration,

68
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:54,034
but the average bird
has five to six air sacs

69
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:57,470
stored away in its chest
and stomach regions.

70
00:03:57,504 --> 00:03:59,439
It’s these pockets of air

71
00:03:59,473 --> 00:04:01,909
that give birds
the ability to remain conscious

72
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:04,478
at altitudes
of 6,000 to 7,000 meters,

73
00:04:04,511 --> 00:04:06,913
a feat completely impossible
for humans.

74
00:04:06,947 --> 00:04:09,383
Even if it were to be strangled,

75
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,652
a bird can survive
for several minutes

76
00:04:11,685 --> 00:04:13,654
thanks to its
internal air reserves.

77
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:15,322
With these advantages,

78
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:18,491
a bird can survive underwater
much longer than a dog.

79
00:04:18,525 --> 00:04:20,527
( Iggy panting )

80
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:27,868
It sounds like something’s
headed straight for me.

81
00:04:27,901 --> 00:04:30,670
But how? That’s impossible!

82
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:33,440
I don’t understand!

83
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:35,308
What could be coming
after me down here?

84
00:04:35,342 --> 00:04:36,910
Wait a sec.

85
00:04:36,944 --> 00:04:37,912
Could it be?

86
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:42,283
( Yells )

87
00:04:42,316 --> 00:04:44,051
( Gasping )

88
00:04:46,486 --> 00:04:48,755
( Pet shop warbles )

89
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:51,058
( Iggy gasps )
It’s that bird again.

90
00:04:51,091 --> 00:04:53,727
But how can it survive
underwater like this?

91
00:04:57,931 --> 00:04:59,933
( Panting )

92
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:04,337
that bastard.
Where’d it fly off to now?

93
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:10,010
( Growls )

94
00:05:15,482 --> 00:05:16,883
( Gasps )

95
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:20,387
It’s closing in,
but what’s its plan?

96
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:23,657
More icicles? One, two, three.

97
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:26,793
Great. Three icicles
are coming this way.

98
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:29,763
( Yells )

99
00:05:35,636 --> 00:05:36,770
( Pet shop squawks )

100
00:05:37,771 --> 00:05:38,872
( Iggy growls )

101
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:42,909
Suck on that, you frickin’ coot!

102
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:49,550
( Pet shop squeals )

103
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:51,552
Iggy: Yes. I did it.

104
00:05:51,585 --> 00:05:53,087
How do you like that?

105
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,556
( Panting )

106
00:06:00,994 --> 00:06:02,996
( Breathing heavily )

107
00:06:04,631 --> 00:06:07,334
The icicles are stopping
the wall from leaking,

108
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,436
but at the rate
they’re spreading,

109
00:06:09,469 --> 00:06:11,604
they’re gonna cover everything!

110
00:06:11,638 --> 00:06:14,141
No. What am I gonna do now?!

111
00:06:15,409 --> 00:06:17,144
( Gasping )

112
00:06:18,679 --> 00:06:20,381
I know what it’s doing.

113
00:06:20,414 --> 00:06:22,950
It’s focusing on freezing
the water around me.

114
00:06:29,156 --> 00:06:31,959
And it’s cut my air pipes.

115
00:06:31,992 --> 00:06:35,529
i-i don’t think
it’s trying to suffocate me.

116
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:37,664
Its real plan
is to Bury me alive.

117
00:06:41,168 --> 00:06:42,970
( Grunting )

118
00:06:43,003 --> 00:06:45,472
It’s no use. It’s collapsing!

119
00:06:45,506 --> 00:06:48,709
This bird is too powerful
for me to hold it off!

120
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:51,845
And what’s worse, i’m surrounded
by ice and freezing water!

121
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:54,415
Just my damn luck.
So much for finding

122
00:06:54,448 --> 00:06:57,718
a decent hiding place
to lay low in for a while.

123
00:06:57,751 --> 00:07:00,420
( Gasps )
No other choice.

124
00:07:00,454 --> 00:07:01,855
I have to dig my way out.

125
00:07:01,889 --> 00:07:03,391
Give me a break.

126
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:05,492
This stupid day has gone
from bad to horrifying

127
00:07:05,526 --> 00:07:06,794
in the worst possible way!

128
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:09,563
First, I lose my leg,
and now some demon bird

129
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:11,631
wants me flattened
into a frozen dinner!

130
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,768
damn.
I can’t hold it off anymore.

131
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:16,770
I’m about to be crushed.

132
00:07:16,803 --> 00:07:19,906
I need to dig myself
out of here now!

133
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:22,075
( Panting )

134
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:27,648
Huh?

135
00:07:27,681 --> 00:07:29,016
What is that?

136
00:07:29,049 --> 00:07:32,019
It looks like someone
dug a tunnel down here,

137
00:07:32,052 --> 00:07:33,086
but why?

138
00:07:36,557 --> 00:07:37,925
( Screams )

139
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:42,763
It’s the bird!

140
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:44,965
it’s getting ready
to shoot another ice missile.

141
00:07:44,998 --> 00:07:46,833
♪

142
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:50,671
damn it. My stand
is being held by the ice.

143
00:07:51,905 --> 00:07:54,074
I can’t defend myself,

144
00:07:54,107 --> 00:07:56,509
and there’s nowhere
for me to escape!

145
00:07:59,713 --> 00:08:01,014
( Gasps )
Wait. That’s it.

146
00:08:01,048 --> 00:08:05,853
Either way you slice it,
it’s do-or-die time!

147
00:08:05,886 --> 00:08:08,055
♪

148
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:12,159
I’ll let the dome break

149
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:13,860
and use the air pressure

150
00:08:13,894 --> 00:08:16,597
to catapult me forward
like a speeding bullet!

151
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:20,667
( Yells )

152
00:08:20,701 --> 00:08:21,969
( Pet shop squawks )

153
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,161
( Iggy gasps )

154
00:08:48,195 --> 00:08:50,164
I got out of there alive.

155
00:08:50,197 --> 00:08:52,299
That dumb bird
didn’t have to die,

156
00:08:52,332 --> 00:08:54,000
but it left me no choice.

157
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:55,736
One of us had to go.

158
00:08:55,769 --> 00:08:57,671
( Shuddering )

159
00:08:59,173 --> 00:09:02,710
But it looks like this’ll
probably be the end for me.

160
00:09:02,743 --> 00:09:05,246
I’ve been bleeding out
for a while now.

161
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:07,915
i hardly have
enough strength in my body

162
00:09:07,948 --> 00:09:11,819
to keep myself afloat,
let alone make it back to shore,

163
00:09:11,852 --> 00:09:13,654
which means i’m gonna drown.

164
00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:17,824
Why is this happening?

165
00:09:17,858 --> 00:09:20,561
I was supposed to live
a trouble-free life.

166
00:09:21,929 --> 00:09:23,964
♪

167
00:10:01,235 --> 00:10:05,039
Damn it. I messed up.

168
00:10:06,406 --> 00:10:08,975
♪

169
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:39,139
( Boy gasps )

170
00:10:39,173 --> 00:10:40,875
Thank goodness I found you.

171
00:10:40,908 --> 00:10:43,244
As soon as I saw
that little face

172
00:10:43,277 --> 00:10:45,846
and those great big ears,
I knew it was you.

173
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:48,215
It’s that stupid bird’s fault
that you’re like this.

174
00:10:48,248 --> 00:10:50,183
It attacked you
just like my dogs.

175
00:10:50,217 --> 00:10:52,720
( Iggy gasps )

176
00:10:52,753 --> 00:10:55,456
( Boy panting )

177
00:10:55,489 --> 00:10:57,291
You’re gonna pull through this.

178
00:10:57,324 --> 00:11:00,327
The bird’s gone, so there’s
nothing to worry about.

179
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,996
Try and hang on, all right?
Keep fighting.

180
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:05,132
I’ll patch you up right away.

181
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:11,204
Narrator: The bird: Pet shop!

182
00:11:11,238 --> 00:11:15,075
Stand: Horus.
Status: Deceased.

183
00:11:18,812 --> 00:11:20,814
( Birds chirping )

184
00:11:26,053 --> 00:11:28,055
( Polnareff groans )
Damn that mangy mutt.

185
00:11:28,088 --> 00:11:30,791
Where the hell
did he run off to?

186
00:11:30,824 --> 00:11:33,060
he’s gotta stop
pulling stunts like this.

187
00:11:33,093 --> 00:11:34,828
Joseph: I’m starting
to get worried.

188
00:11:34,862 --> 00:11:36,664
He’s been gone for a while.

189
00:11:36,697 --> 00:11:39,099
Polnareff: That lousy flea bag.

190
00:11:39,132 --> 00:11:41,434
( Jotaro gasps ) Huh?

191
00:11:42,636 --> 00:11:44,071
Joseph: Jotaro,
what’s the matter?

192
00:11:46,807 --> 00:11:49,176
Avdol: There must be
someone following us again.

193
00:11:52,646 --> 00:11:53,914
Jotaro: Not quite,

194
00:11:53,947 --> 00:11:55,682
but I thought I heard a voice,

195
00:11:55,716 --> 00:11:57,785
like someone’s
calling out to us.

196
00:11:57,818 --> 00:11:59,920
- Polnareff: Hmm.
- Joseph: A voice?

197
00:11:59,953 --> 00:12:01,354
Avdol: Hmm?

198
00:12:01,388 --> 00:12:03,390
( Iggy whimpering )

199
00:12:09,596 --> 00:12:11,998
Avdol: It’s iggy!

200
00:12:18,038 --> 00:12:19,172
Joseph: Hmm?

201
00:12:19,206 --> 00:12:20,574
Polnareff: Iggy!

202
00:12:22,543 --> 00:12:24,145
Avdol: What on earth happened?!

203
00:12:24,178 --> 00:12:25,813
Joseph: Look at that.

204
00:12:25,846 --> 00:12:27,648
He’s got injuries
all over his body.

205
00:12:27,681 --> 00:12:30,784
Polnareff: Hey, iggy’s missing
his front leg, too!

206
00:12:30,817 --> 00:12:33,953
joseph: You think
he got run over by a car?

207
00:12:33,987 --> 00:12:37,691
Avdol: He’s not the kind of dog
that gets into car accidents.

208
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:42,129
You were attacked by the enemy,
weren’t you?

209
00:12:43,564 --> 00:12:44,832
Joseph: What’s this?

210
00:12:44,865 --> 00:12:47,735
it looks as though
someone treated his wounds.

211
00:12:47,768 --> 00:12:50,671
i have to say
they did a great job.

212
00:12:50,704 --> 00:12:52,172
( Polnareff sighs )

213
00:12:52,206 --> 00:12:54,642
Jotaro: But it wasn’t iggy
that I heard.

214
00:12:54,675 --> 00:12:58,179
Whoever was calling out to us
was definitely human.

215
00:12:58,212 --> 00:13:00,014
- Joseph: Huh?
- Polnareff: Huh?

216
00:13:00,047 --> 00:13:04,084
Kakyoin: Iggy did have
a run-in with the enemy.

217
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:07,921
When we found him, he was
half-dead in the arms of a boy,

218
00:13:07,955 --> 00:13:11,459
so the speedwagon foundation
doctors saw to his wounds.

219
00:13:11,491 --> 00:13:14,728
They did the same...

220
00:13:14,761 --> 00:13:15,829
For my eyes.

221
00:13:15,863 --> 00:13:16,831
Polnareff: It’s you!

222
00:13:16,864 --> 00:13:18,532
You’re finally back!

223
00:13:18,565 --> 00:13:20,567
♪

224
00:13:25,072 --> 00:13:26,040
( Kakyoin chuckles )

225
00:13:26,073 --> 00:13:28,642
All: It’s kakyoin!

226
00:13:28,675 --> 00:13:30,544
polnareff:
Good to see you, kakyoin!

227
00:13:30,577 --> 00:13:32,612
- how’s it going?
- Avdol: Kakyoin, tell me,

228
00:13:32,646 --> 00:13:34,248
how are your eyes treating you?

229
00:13:34,281 --> 00:13:36,150
Kakyoin: I’m glad
you’re all safe.

230
00:13:36,183 --> 00:13:38,986
Joseph: We missed you, pal.
( Laughs )

231
00:13:39,019 --> 00:13:40,921
So they were able to treat you?

232
00:13:40,954 --> 00:13:42,589
kakyoin: Yes.
I’m ready for action.

233
00:13:42,623 --> 00:13:44,925
While it’s true
i’ll have a few scars,

234
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:46,726
my eyesight is back to normal.

235
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,996
Joseph: We’re all really glad
to hear that.

236
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,735
Kakyoin: Jotaro.

237
00:13:54,768 --> 00:13:55,869
( Jotaro grunts )

238
00:13:55,903 --> 00:13:57,638
( Iggy panting )

239
00:13:57,671 --> 00:13:59,640
( Growls )

240
00:13:59,673 --> 00:14:00,807
Joseph: Hmm?

241
00:14:02,042 --> 00:14:04,645
Where do you think
you’re going, iggy?

242
00:14:05,879 --> 00:14:07,647
Kakyoin: He may have
been quite indifferent

243
00:14:07,681 --> 00:14:09,483
toward humans and stands
in the past,

244
00:14:09,516 --> 00:14:12,219
but now it looks like he’s
trying to lead us somewhere.

245
00:14:12,252 --> 00:14:14,588
I’m not aware of all the details

246
00:14:14,621 --> 00:14:16,790
surrounding his encounter
with the enemy stand,

247
00:14:16,823 --> 00:14:20,060
but judging from his resolve,
this is about revenge.

248
00:14:20,093 --> 00:14:22,228
Joseph: Maybe, but that
still doesn’t explain

249
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:23,663
where he’s taking us.

250
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:25,699
Polnareff: Hang on, iggy!
wait for us!

251
00:14:25,732 --> 00:14:27,133
Avdol: Hmm?

252
00:14:38,745 --> 00:14:40,046
- Joseph: Huh?
- ( Kakyoin gasps )

253
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,816
Joseph: I recognize that car.

254
00:14:44,985 --> 00:14:48,322
It’s the same fancy ride
the beggar was driving.

255
00:14:48,355 --> 00:14:50,891
C-could this wreckage
mean that he...

256
00:14:50,924 --> 00:14:52,259
( Polnareff and kakyoin gasp )

257
00:14:52,292 --> 00:14:54,761
Polnareff: But how?
What’s strong enough

258
00:14:54,795 --> 00:14:58,265
to tear a hole through a car
like a piece of wet newspaper?

259
00:14:58,298 --> 00:14:59,866
Avdol: It would seem as though

260
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:02,202
i was right
to be concerned about him.

261
00:15:02,236 --> 00:15:04,105
He should have
never been involved.

262
00:15:04,137 --> 00:15:06,873
Joseph: Is it possible
this is the handiwork

263
00:15:06,907 --> 00:15:09,276
of the stand user
iggy fought earlier?

264
00:15:09,309 --> 00:15:11,978
Avdol: All signs seem to point
to that being the case.

265
00:15:12,012 --> 00:15:13,080
Joseph: Huh? Iggy!

266
00:15:13,113 --> 00:15:14,114
Avdol: Hmm?

267
00:15:15,115 --> 00:15:17,117
( Iggy growling )

268
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:22,089
( Gasping )

269
00:15:22,122 --> 00:15:24,124
♪

270
00:15:30,164 --> 00:15:32,133
polnareff:
What the hell’s going on?

271
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:35,336
all of a sudden,
i’m drenched in a cold sweat,

272
00:15:35,369 --> 00:15:37,938
and there’s
this oppressive feeling of doom

273
00:15:37,971 --> 00:15:39,139
roaming in the air.

274
00:15:40,407 --> 00:15:42,309
( Jotaro grunts )

275
00:15:42,342 --> 00:15:45,312
polnareff:
I don’t know about you guys,

276
00:15:45,345 --> 00:15:47,180
but I am majorly creeped out.

277
00:15:47,214 --> 00:15:50,084
where exactly
is iggy trying to take us?

278
00:15:53,353 --> 00:15:55,956
Joseph: I know where he’s going.

279
00:15:55,989 --> 00:15:58,725
this feeling,
it’s all too familiar to me.

280
00:15:59,893 --> 00:16:02,929
this aura
is pure, unmitigated evil.

281
00:16:05,032 --> 00:16:06,133
( Men grunt )

282
00:16:09,336 --> 00:16:11,405
Avdol: It’s the mansion
from the picture.

283
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:14,775
Jotaro: We’ve arrived.

284
00:16:16,777 --> 00:16:19,880
Polnareff: Iggy, you were
able to find it by yourself?

285
00:16:19,913 --> 00:16:21,915
♪

286
00:16:23,217 --> 00:16:24,952
( Men grunt )

287
00:16:27,054 --> 00:16:28,355
( Iggy grunts )

288
00:16:29,857 --> 00:16:32,360
narrator: What lay
before jotaro and the others

289
00:16:32,392 --> 00:16:33,927
was something more sinister

290
00:16:33,961 --> 00:16:35,963
than anything
they’d previously faced.

291
00:16:35,996 --> 00:16:39,233
They would soon look upon
the source of their predicament

292
00:16:39,266 --> 00:16:41,869
and the very embodiment of evil.

293
00:16:41,902 --> 00:16:45,839
The path that had led them here
was long and arduous.

294
00:16:45,873 --> 00:16:48,342
Foreign lands
shrouded in mystery

295
00:16:48,375 --> 00:16:50,010
and treacherous
stand-using assassins

296
00:16:50,043 --> 00:16:51,845
met them at every step.

297
00:16:51,879 --> 00:16:54,348
each battle was
a struggle for survival

298
00:16:54,381 --> 00:16:57,284
where the wrong move
would spell out certain death.

299
00:16:57,317 --> 00:17:03,190
There were tears, laughter,
sadness, rage, and joy.

300
00:17:03,223 --> 00:17:06,259
- The journey affected them all.
- ( Singing in Japanese )

301
00:17:06,293 --> 00:17:09,029
Narrator: Now nearly
50 days have passed

302
00:17:09,062 --> 00:17:11,197
since the team departed Japan
on their quest

303
00:17:11,231 --> 00:17:14,034
to save the life
of jotaro’s mother Holly.

304
00:17:15,135 --> 00:17:16,370
Everything led to this.

305
00:17:16,403 --> 00:17:18,839
The time had come to defeat dio

306
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:21,842
and end the hundred-year curse
afflicting the joestar family.

307
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:25,011
Joseph was determined
to save his daughter Holly,

308
00:17:25,045 --> 00:17:29,016
and nothing and no one
was going to stand in his way.

309
00:17:29,049 --> 00:17:31,385
Kakyoin vowed
to remain resolute.

310
00:17:31,418 --> 00:17:34,388
He would defeat dio
not only to save Holly,

311
00:17:34,421 --> 00:17:37,724
but to overcome
his own weaknesses.

312
00:17:37,758 --> 00:17:40,394
Avdol was steadfast
in his conviction,

313
00:17:40,427 --> 00:17:42,329
considering it his personal duty

314
00:17:42,362 --> 00:17:45,065
to root out evil
wherever it lurked.

315
00:17:45,098 --> 00:17:48,301
Polnareff was determined
to make the tyrant dio suffer

316
00:17:48,335 --> 00:17:50,304
for turning him into a puppet

317
00:17:50,337 --> 00:17:54,107
and forcing him
to betray his own principles.

318
00:17:54,141 --> 00:17:56,443
Iggy’s spirit was untamable.

319
00:17:56,476 --> 00:17:58,378
He knew his life of turmoil

320
00:17:58,412 --> 00:18:01,248
could be traced back
to a single man

321
00:18:01,281 --> 00:18:05,051
and was intent on making sure
the bastard faced his wrath.

322
00:18:05,085 --> 00:18:06,853
And so...

323
00:18:06,887 --> 00:18:08,088
Jotaro: In other words,

324
00:18:08,121 --> 00:18:10,824
if we beat the shit
out of dio in there,

325
00:18:10,858 --> 00:18:13,361
this damn nightmare
will be over once and for all.

326
00:18:13,393 --> 00:18:15,395
- ( Iggy growls )
- Joseph: That’s right,

327
00:18:15,429 --> 00:18:18,232
and the scent of evil
confirms that he’s here.

328
00:18:18,265 --> 00:18:21,301
He’s hiding inside the mansion
like the coward he is.

329
00:18:21,335 --> 00:18:23,037
Avdol: It’s hard
to believe, but...

330
00:18:24,304 --> 00:18:25,505
polnareff:
We’ve finally reached the end

331
00:18:25,539 --> 00:18:27,241
of this hellacious journey.

332
00:18:27,274 --> 00:18:29,743
Joseph: All right,
men, you ready?

333
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:31,111
( Men grunt )

334
00:18:36,850 --> 00:18:38,852
♪

335
00:18:44,157 --> 00:18:47,394
iggy: The gate’s open
as if they’re inviting us in.

336
00:18:47,427 --> 00:18:50,297
This is totally different
from the situation yesterday.

337
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:52,065
( Joseph grunts )

338
00:18:53,066 --> 00:18:54,067
( Men grunt )

339
00:18:54,101 --> 00:18:55,569
♪

340
00:19:02,309 --> 00:19:05,479
Joseph: Now that I think
about it, if I can sense dio,

341
00:19:05,512 --> 00:19:06,947
then it stands to reason

342
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:09,082
that he has the ability
to sense us, too.

343
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:15,756
If we try to enter
the mansion guns blazing,

344
00:19:15,789 --> 00:19:18,492
no doubt we’ll be playing
right into the enemy’s hands.

345
00:19:18,525 --> 00:19:23,296
before we do anything,
we need to think of a strategy.

346
00:19:28,335 --> 00:19:29,536
- ( Men gasp )
- Joseph: Careful!

347
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:31,939
The door is opening!
Everyone on guard!

348
00:19:31,972 --> 00:19:33,974
( Creaking )

349
00:19:35,576 --> 00:19:38,145
Joseph: Hmm? ( Grunts )

350
00:19:48,288 --> 00:19:51,858
polnareff: Check it out.
What’s with this weird corridor?

351
00:19:51,892 --> 00:19:55,396
It must go on forever.
This can’t be real, right?

352
00:19:55,429 --> 00:19:57,898
It has to be some sort
of trick or illusion.

353
00:19:57,931 --> 00:19:59,533
joseph: Listen.
Polnareff, no matter what,

354
00:19:59,566 --> 00:20:01,234
don’t go through the door.

355
00:20:01,268 --> 00:20:03,337
Dio’s probably got
a couple more stand users

356
00:20:03,370 --> 00:20:05,272
waiting in the wings
to fight us.

357
00:20:05,305 --> 00:20:06,907
- ( Both gasp )
- Polnareff: Hey!

358
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:08,542
Something’s coming this way!

359
00:20:08,575 --> 00:20:11,511
♪

360
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:13,247
Wait. Is that guy floating?

361
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:15,516
Is he a stand user or what?

362
00:20:30,364 --> 00:20:32,533
Man: Master joestar...

363
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:35,435
Welcome to our abode.

364
00:20:35,469 --> 00:20:37,271
We’ve been expecting you, sir.

365
00:20:37,304 --> 00:20:40,440
I am the resident Butler
of the mansion.

366
00:20:45,579 --> 00:20:47,581
♪

